node.text:
I’m not sure how I did it, but I did 20 minutes inside the ice bath.  I blame @jockowillink’s kid!
The @morozkoforge cold plunge keeps this thing at a steady 33 degrees Fahrenheit.  It’s fucking wild. 
I was shivering after this for a solid 30 minutes.  I drove to work, it’s 90 degrees out in Texas and I had the AC off and I was shivering the whole way to work.

node.text:
These UFO videos keep coming, and they’re getting weirder and weirder.  Now they’re going underwater. 

Repost: @jeremycorbell The US Navy photographed and filmed “spherical” shaped UFOs and advanced transmedium vehicles; here is some of that footage.

This footage was filmed in the CIC (Combat Information Center) of the USS Omaha on July 15th 2019 in a warning area off San Diego. This footage depicts a UAP event series that reached a crescendo with one of the unknown targets entering the water. No wreckage found. None of the unknown craft were recovered.

LOCATION OF SHIP
32°29'21.9”N 119°21'53.0”W

TIME OF EVENT (SUBMERSION)
11pm PST (6am GMT - indicated a day ahead on display)

ADDITIONAL DETAILS
• Minimum 14 targets.
• Minimum 6ft in diameter - solid mass.
• Varying speeds from 40 kts - 138 kts (46 mph - 158 mph).
• Flight lasting longer than an hour.
• Unknowns were illuminated.
• Unable to discern origin, nor launch or landing points.
• Unknown vehicles picked up on more than two types of RADAR.
• Still images of this footage were included in the May 1st, 2020 UAPTF intelligence briefing that I have previously reported on.
• It is noted in intelligence reports that the “spherical” craft appeared to be transmedium capable, and were observed descending into the water without destruction.
• It is noted in intelligence reports that the “spherical” craft could not be found upon entry to the water - that a submarine was used in the search - and recovered nothing.
• This footage is unclassified.
• Craft remain officially - unidentified.

We do not know what, if anything, the Navy or Pentagon might be willing to say about the USS Omaha incident, but we are confident the incident is a legitimate mystery and look forward to whatever information might be forthcoming.

Go get ‘em tigers!

Your pal,

Jeremy (aka 4Name)

node.text:
This is a part of a very disturbing but important conversation I had with @drshannaswan about how chemicals from plastics and pesticides are radically reducing sperm counts and increasing miscarriages.  It’s some really scary shit. 

Posted @withregram • @joeroganexperience Ep 1638 - @drshannaswan explains how phthalates get into our bodies. 
•Shanna Swan, Ph.D, is an environmental and reproductive epidemiologist whose work examines the impact of chemical exposure on reproductive health and child development. Her book “Count Down” is available now.

node.title: Chemicals from plastics are altering human babies.

node.text:
I love watching the process of archery practice pay off.  It’s so fucking satisfying.  When that arrow leaves the bow and perfectly finds its mark it’s like there’s nothing else happening in the world at that moment. 
“Nothing clears a troubled mind like shooting a bow.” - Fred Bear.

node.text:
One of my best friends, and one of my favorite people on earth, the great and powerful @cameronrhanes wrote a book. 
Thanks to you guys it’s already soaring up the charts just on preorders.  I wrote the forward to it, and he promised me if the book does well he’s finally going to quit his day job! Cam is one of the most exceptional people I’ve ever met, and his book is excellent and truly inspiring. 

Repost: @cameronrhanes ENDURE by Cameron Hanes is written. ✅

And, today, is called the “cover reveal” and the first day the book can be ordered. 

The complete manuscript has been submitted. Now, it’s in the hands of one of the biggest and most successful book publishers in New York, @stmartinspress, who are in the business of churning out NYT best selling hit after hit. 

Can some nobody bowhunter grinding out a 9-5 while chasing his true purpose in the mountains live up to the publisher’s vision for my book? Time will tell. I’ve buck the odds my whole life, might as well continue this, “born to lose, built to win” theme. 

I’m extremely honored that @joerogan wrote the foreword to ENDURE. We’ve included an excerpt here (swipe 👈) as well as an excerpt from the legendary @davidgoggins (swipe 👈). Two amazing men I’m proud to call friends. 

Aside from that my book will be 304 pages, hard back and full of many life lessons. And of course it is ripe with plenty of bumps, bruises, heartaches, triumphs and forks in the road as I navigate my way from small town nobody to earning incredible opportunities through my bowhunting passion. Opportunities like learning and training with Olympic heroes, incredible endurance athletes, championship caliber UFC fighters, larger-than-life living legends like Goggins not to mention some of the greatest mountain bowhunters who’ve ever walked the planet. I’ve shared tidbits of the wisdom I’ve learned over the years from rubbing elbows with these OUTLIERS and from bowhunting wild and famous country for iconic animals within the pages of ENDURE. 

Pre order my book now at the link in my bio above 👆 and you’ll be one of the very first to get a copy of ENDURE. 

Thank you. 🙏

node.text:
I’m not sure how I did it, but I did 20 minutes inside the ice bath.  I blame @jockowillink’s kid!
The @morozkoforge cold plunge keeps this thing at a steady 33 degrees Fahrenheit.  It’s fucking wild. 
I was shivering after this for a solid 30 minutes.  I drove to work, it’s 90 degrees out in Texas and I had the AC off and I was shivering the whole way to work.

node.text: This is a real sleeper card on tonight.  The main event between @tjdillashaw and @enterthesandman135 is a huge fight for the bantamweight division and a real puzzle.  @punahele_soriano vs @b_allen185 is about to go right now, and both guys are super talented.  Allen has some slick submission skills and Soriano is a crusher! @adrianyanez93 is one of the hottest prospects at 135 and he’s got a real test in @randy_costa.  I’m hyped!
